The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sport
		 Friday, October 24, 2003  IN THE CITY
				 																																																	 The CAB will pay a service tax of Rs 50,000 to the Calcutta Municipal Corporation for the tri-series final on November 18. The CAB president Jagmohan Dalmiya met the Mayor Subrata Mukherjee on Thursday to finalise the decision. The CAB will henceforth pay the same amount for every international match.				 																																																	 The Bangladesh under-15 team thrashed their CAB counterparts by eight wickets in a friendly one-dayer on Thursday.				 																																																	BRIEF SCORES: CAB U-15 XI 132 in 36 ovs. Bangladesh U-15 XI 133/2 in 37.2 ovs. Bangladesh U-15 won by eight wickets.				 																																																	 Saurav Kothari and Barneet Kohli made the final of the BRC state junior snooker meet at the Bengal Rowing Club on Thursday. Sourav and Barneet beat Ankit Kejriwal and Anurag Bagri, respectively.
